  "text": "With an additional variation in experimental parameters, one study on high day temperature also restricted the period of exposure to specific daylight hours. No changes in total anthocyanins were observed when high temperature was applied in the early morning and late evening in Pinot Noir [CITATION_1] . This suggests that mid-day temperature had the most impact Fig. 4 . Fold changes in colour or total anthocyanins (treatment/control) at maturity depending on the phenological stage at which the experiment is conducted and in relation to three experimental parameters: dT=difference in temperature between heated and control (A), T mean =average temperature of the heated treatment (B), and time of exposure (C). Data are compiled from all publications listed in Table 1 .",
